[Migrating from JIRA Cloud to Server applications|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/migrating-from-jira-cloud-to-server-applications-802592270.html] currently has many mentions of quite old JIRA versions:
{quote}
This is because we have introduced features from the upcoming JIRA server application version into JIRA cloud applications. For example, the latest JIRA server application release is JIRA 6.2.x. JIRA 6.3 is currently under development.
{quote}
This is in the 7.1 and 7.2 versions of that page, at least.

In addition, the version matrix at the bottom of that has a latest listed version from 2013. Even if the guideline to "always use the latest" is the recommendation, it seems strange to have such a big gap.

Some information about if it is possible to import Cloud to a not-quite-latest version might also be useful in that case. If not, maybe a note about loss of configuration and some data, coupled with a link to CSV export/import information would help point people the direction of one alternative.

