h3. Problem Description

If task has a few subtasks and all of them are tagged to a version, they will be counted in Roadmap gadget.

h3. Suggested Resolution

Provide an option for Roadmap gadget to exclude the parent task.

h3. Customer's comment

{quote}
My concern is as below with example
Suppose I have one task with four subtask the road map is showing remaining issue left 5 where as if I complete all the 4 subtask then the above task gets closed automatically. In that case the roadmap should have counted remaining activity as four not five more over task and sub task are not issues as per the JIRA definition of issue

So proposal is roadmap should not say remaining issues instead it should say remaining activity and it should not count count the task whenever there are subtask is attached to it
{quote}

