As a co-branded team, we would like the ability to have a release burndown based on a status other than "Resolved".  Our workflow is such that after a feature is completed on our side, it goes for customer acceptance and testing -- areas over which we have no control.  The release burndown assumes a status of "resolved/done" to show any data and while that works in many cases, it would be nice to specify per burndown which status is "done" for your team.  This gives everyone the chance to use this functionality as features flow from team to team.

I ran into this issue as well when fixing production defects that were reported by the customer.  The customer is the one who could say they were "done" that would take them months sometimes.  However, development and QA were done with them almost right away and to track SLAs we needed to associate "resolved" with different statuses which was not possible with JIRA.

Not sure if we are not using the software correctly or there is a better way but frequently features and defects originate outside the development team, are fixed/developed by DEV, and are finally closed by the reporters.  I think this is a pretty common practice in Professional Service Development Teams and having the ability to report a status as resolved that we specify would make JIRA more powerful for all.
